The agents maintain information on who's connected and what they are doing,
the current status of all nodes, the global state of the database, and a
list of people that should be notified of any changes.  All of this
information is important in strong collaboration because, in strong
collaboration, each participant contributes to each section of the artifact
as it is being developed.  In order to contribute to each section, each
participant must know the current state of the sections.  That current
state includes who is working on it and any changes to the contents.  The
AEN agents help maintain the information necessary for the process of
strong collaboration.
