The issues of collaborating to develop hypertext documents are becoming
more and more important each day.  The use of hypertext as a structuring
mechanism for richly interdependent information is becoming more
widespread, and finds application in many areas of software engineering and
other fields.
d32 7
a38 4
This research is concerned with how people collaboratively author and
learn.  More specifically, it is concerned with how to design and implement
a hypertext system to support strong collaboration in authoring and learning. 
We define strong collaboration as:
a39 1
\begin{quote}
a40 13
  By ``strong collaboration'', we mean to evoke situations in which a group
  synergistically develops and improves a structured artifact more
  efficiently and effectively than would be possible by the same group of
  people working independently.\cite{csdl-94-20}

\end{quote}


We are investigating collaborative authoring, learning and strong
collaboration through the design, implementation, and evaluation of AEN
\footnote{Annotated Egret Navigator}, a hypertext collaborative authoring
and learning tool.

